commit.message:
git_r3.py: Handle empty output of git ls-remote

With recent trend of renaming master branches, it's easy to get
empty output of git ls-remote, esp. if given ebuild wasn't
updated yet. Unfortunately, git returns 0 which makes it
impossible for us, the caller, to distinguish this error.

At any rate, when git returned no output, then
__init__.py  calls parseoutput(out='') but git_r3 implementation
doesn't handle this case properly. Fix that.

Signed-off-by: Michal Privoznik <mprivozn@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

verification.payload:
tree 20adb19c544b874c0d8a66294cc58d8b44575821
parent f0f0c2327aa58d642e3b4450b4097f68e557e465
author Michal Privoznik <mprivozn@redhat.com> 1644092208 +0100
committer Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org> 1644134781 +0100

git_r3.py: Handle empty output of git ls-remote

With recent trend of renaming master branches, it's easy to get
empty output of git ls-remote, esp. if given ebuild wasn't
updated yet. Unfortunately, git returns 0 which makes it
impossible for us, the caller, to distinguish this error.

At any rate, when git returned no output, then
__init__.py  calls parseoutput(out='') but git_r3 implementation
doesn't handle this case properly. Fix that.

Signed-off-by: Michal Privoznik <mprivozn@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

commit.message:
Pass --getbinpkg=n by default

Similarly to #7, disable `getbinpkg` which might be the default, for example
with `FEATURES=getbinpkg`.

Closes: https://github.com/mgorny/smart-live-rebuild/pull/8
Bump to 1.3.6

cli: Pass --usepkg=n by default

Some users set --usepkg in EMERGE_DEFAULT_OPTS, but it obviously makes
no sense to remerge a binary package if we already decided it needs to
be rebuilt.

Closes: https://github.com/mgorny/smart-live-rebuild/pull/7
Bump to 1.3.5

vcs: Preserve GIT_PROXY_COMMAND

Closes: https://bitbucket.org/mgorny/smart-live-rebuild/issues/8

Revert pkg_needrebuild() support

The pkg_needrebuild() code is buggy and terribly slow. Revert it until
someone finds time to fix and improve it.
pkg_needrebuild: do not repeat CPV in output head
Support rebuilding through pkg_needrebuild() function
vim: set noet explicitly everywhere
Bump PV to 1.3.4.1

Fix missing quoting in git-r3 support

Fixes: https://bugs.gentoo.org/show_bug.cgi?id=531530
Bump PV to 1.3.4.
Remove version checks for portage, old API is unsupported now.
Pass all_count through IPC when forking.
Print complete live package count as well.
Bump PV to 1.3.3.
